column168: DURING SHIPPING PAIL HAD FALLEN UP AGAINST TRAILER DOOR. WHEN DOOR WAS OPENED, BOLT FROM DOOR DAMAGED PAIL CAUSING SPILL.
The supersack appeared to have been forked.
column169: Exercise caution when loading or unloading freight.

column62: Impact with Sharp or Protruding Object (e.g., nails)
column168: While unloading drums noticed a puddle under the drum. It was found that the drum body had a hole in it and material leaked out. Drum was placed in overpack, and material cleaned up in house. The hole was caused by a bolt from another drum.
column172: Container, no description given (do not use if at all possible)
